<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-04-28T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-04-28T04:00:00-05:00" n="784" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d784">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6731/102: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-28T11:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">April
                                        28</hi>[<hi rend="italic">29?</hi>], <hi rend="italic">1928—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received April 29—4:55
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>63. Am orally informed by Foreign Office that Council of Ministers has
                            approved prolongation of commercial <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi>
                            with the United States until April 10, 1929, according to existing
                            provisions of law.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>